pageContext.claim: “You had 109 people out of hundreds of thousands of travelers and all we did was vet those people very, very carefully. ...  It was 109 people.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump’s figures on the scope of the travel ban were ludicrously low. The universe of people likely affected by the travel suspension was around 60,000, according to the State Department — not 109. The White House later admitted the 109 figure reflected only the number of people who were affected by the ban and were in-flight at the time the order was signed
